helptext sub_stn_156_help =
 "
 **** SUB STATION 156 POPUP MIMIC ****
 ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------
Southern Airside Road - Substation 156 
 ------------------------------------------------- -------------------------------------------------

This Mimic displays circuit breaker status, current and voltage for Panels on Substation 156.


HV Mimic
The Circuit Breakers are Control and Monitoring. 

The Analogue meters display high and low alarms together with under/over/invalid ranges.
Low and High alarms may be set by the operator. The meter can also be tagged.

Maximum Demand meters are also shown (display only)

LV Mimic Popup
Substation 156 houses 2 off 11/0.415kV transformers for the supply of local equipment via an LV switchboard.
The statuses of the local transformers and the LV ACBs are displayed via the LV popup mimic (TX1 and TX2 objects).

FEGP
A Navigation Button is provided for Sub 156 FEGP status mimic


References:
------------------
Operation and Maintenance Manual 	- 

Keypages from the Mimic Menu Object -  for information on mimic objects used (HV Area)
 ------------------

 "

